article.headline: Boise St. 67, UC Davis 47
article.story: DAVIS, Calif. -- La'Shard Anderson scored 18 points to lead four Boise State players in double figures and the Broncos pulled away in the second half for a 67-47 victory over UC Davis on Sunday. Robert Arnold added 13 points, Ryan Watkins and Paul Noonan each had 11 and Leon Rice became the first Boise State coach to win his first three games since the school became a four-year institution prior to the 1968-69 season. Joe Harden had a team-high 15 points for the Aggies (1-4), who led 26-24 at halftime thanks to a 10-1 run. A layup by Watkins with 13:32 to play gave Boise State its first lead of the second half, 34-32, and the Broncos later pulled away for good with a 12-0 run. Watkins, a freshman, finished with a game-high nine rebounds.
